## ASG ##

Application security group enables you to configure network security, allowing you to group virtual machines and define network security policies based on those groups.
  - ASGs can be set as source or destination on an NSG
  - NSGs would still be required if the VMs are grouped together with ASGs
ASGs -> logical grouping of VMs

NSG | NIC

NIC is a device similar to a hardware device connected to our personal device.
NSG is a security group inside the virtual network.

devops    - general information on all the devops tools
devsecops - security in each layer,

GIT security:
    does not allow even local commit, if the file has any access related informations like access keys.
